2026-06-24 03:37:37,513 DEBUG msg #229: assistant (tool_use) tool_use(Bash): {'command': 'cd "/Volumes/External SSD/worldcup-2026-prediction" && gh issue create \\\n  --title "feat: group-stage simulation engine with FIFA tiebreaks (simulation/group_stage.py)" \\\n  --milestone "Cycle 5 — Tournament Simulation & Full Pipeline" \\\n  --label "phase:implement,priority:high,area:simulation,agent:python-pro" \\\n  --assignee "@me" \\\n  --body "$(cat <<\'EOF\'\n## Goal\nGiven a live `TournamentState` (played WC2026 results held fixed + remaining fixtures) and a Dixon-Coles `ScorelineSampler`, simulate the remaining group matches and produce final standings for all 12 groups, ranked by the full FIFA tiebreak chain. This is the first half of the live simulator; its output feeds Round-of-32 resolution.\n\n## Context\n`data/live.py` exposes `TournamentState` (`live.py:106-113`) which partitions into `played: list[LiveMatch]`, `remaining_group_fixtures: list[LiveMatch]`, and `standings: list[GroupStanding]`. `LiveMatch` (`live.py:21-62`) carries `home_team, away_team, group, home_goals, away_goals, neutral` (names already normalized via `crosswalk.normalize_team`). `GroupStanding` (`live.py:96-103`) holds `group, stage, table` rows.\n\n`simulation/poisson.py` provides the scoreline sampler: `ScorelineSampler.sample(home, away, neutral=False, size=1, random_state=None) -> np.ndarray` returns shape `(size, 2)` `[home_goals, away_goals]` arrays, seeded by `random_state` or `config.random_seed` (`poisson.py:241-256`). Use `make_sampler(abilities, config)` / `fit_dixon_coles(df, config)` factories.\n\n**Critical downstream contract:** `data/wc2026_bracket.py:resolve_r32(standings)` consumes standings as a **dict** `{group_letter: [row_dict, ...]}` where each row dict has football-data.org v4 keys (`team` with nested `name`, `points`, `goalDifference`, `goalsFor`, `position`). `rank_third_places()` (`wc2026_bracket.py:157-166`) also consumes that dict shape. So this engine must emit standings in that v4 dict shape, not as `GroupStanding` objects.\n\nWC2026 is mostly neutral venues → `home_advantage = 0` for neutral matches (the sampler already handles `neutral`). FIFA group tiebreak order: points → goal difference → goals for → head-to-head (points/GD/GF among tied teams) → seeded coin-flip.\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] New `GroupStageSimulator` (or pure functions) ingests `TournamentState`: played `LiveMatch` goals are held FIXED and never resampled; only `remaining_group_fixtures` are sampled via `ScorelineSampler`.\n- [ ] Accumulates points (3/1/0), goals-for, goals-against, goal-difference per team across fixed + sampled results.\n- [ ] Ranks each group by the full FIFA tiebreak chain: points → goal-diff → goals-for → head-to-head → seeded coin-flip (using the injected RNG, not `random`/`Math.random`).\n- [ ] Emits final standings in the v4 dict shape `{group: [{team:{name}, position, points, goalDifference, goalsFor, ...}]}` consumed by `wc2026_bracket.resolve_r32`.\n- [ ] Deterministic given a seed: identical `TournamentState` + seed → identical standings across runs.\n- [ ] All tests pass; new `tests/test_group_stage.py` exercises each tiebreak rung with constructed ties and asserts played results are never resampled.\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #16: feat: Cycle 5 config groundwork — [rf]/[odds] sections, knockout sim params, TOML wiring\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Create:** `worldcup_playoff/simulation/group_stage.py` — `GroupStageSimulator` consuming a `ScorelineSampler` + seed/config; small helpers for point accumulation, FIFA tiebreak ordering, and the `GroupStanding`/sampled-rows → v4-dict adapter.\n- **Create:** `tests/test_group_stage.py` — feed a synthetic `TournamentState` (some played, some remaining) + a stub/deterministic sampler; assert tiebreak ordering and fixed-result invariance; assert seed reproducibility.\n- Inject the RNG (`numpy.random.Generator`) for the coin-flip rung so it is seed-deterministic. Do not call `Date.now()`/`random` directly.\n- Keep the v4-dict adapter as a named helper so the knockout task can reuse the exact shape `resolve_r32` expects.\n- Do not modify the existing `simulation/tournament.py` (it remains the legacy fixed-bracket, classifier-based simulator — keep the ~248 tests green).\nEOF\n)"', 'description': 'Create issue #17 (group-stage sim)'}
