eds so two runs with the same seed produce identical odds.\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] Orchestrates: ingest `TournamentState` → fit/accept `TeamAbilities` once → loop N tournaments (group sim from #17 + knockout from #18) with per-iteration sub-seeds derived from a master seed → accumulate champion + round-reached counts.\n- [ ] Returns a `ForecastResult` value object with full title odds (champion probability per team, all 48 teams present) and `{round: probabilities}` per-round advancement reusing the `RoundResult.probabilities` contract.\n- [ ] Title-odds across all 48 teams sum to ≈ 1.0; per-round advancement counts match the number of slots in each round.\n- [ ] Runs **no-key by default** (martj42 WC2026 schedule); football-data.org key optional for live refinement; re-runnable after each matchday.\n- [ ] Deterministic: same master seed → identical odds across two runs.\n- [ ] ~100k tournaments complete in seconds–low minutes (document the measured timing).\n- [ ] All tests pass; new `tests/test_live_forecast.py` runs a small-N forecast with a stub sampler asserting probability sanity, 48-team coverage, and seed reproducibility.\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #16: feat: Cycle 5 config groundwork — [rf]/[odds] sections, knockout sim params, TOML wiring\n- #17: feat: group-stage simulation engine with FIFA tiebreaks (simulation/group_stage.py)\n- #18: feat: R32 resolution + single-elimination knockout sim with extra-time/penalties (simulation/knockout.py)\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Create:** `worldcup_playoff/simulation/live_forecast.py` — orchestrator function/class returning `ForecastResult`; derive per-iteration sub-seeds from the `SimulationConfig.random_seed` (issue #16) via a `numpy.random.SeedSequence`/spawn pattern for reproducible parallel-safe streams.\n- **Create:** `tests/test_live_forecast.py` — small N (e.g. 200) with stub sampler: assert champion probs sum ≈ 1.0 over 48 teams, all teams present, two runs identical under same seed.\n- Keep the existing `simulation/tournament.py` untouched; this is a sibling orchestrator (do not overload the legacy classifier-based simulator).\n- Fit Dixon-Coles abilities **once** outside the Monte-Carlo loop for performance; vectorize scoreline sampling where possible (the sampler accepts `size=N`).\n- No-key default is a hard requirement — guard the live-adapter path so a missing key degrades to the martj42 schedule rather than raising.\nEOF\n)"', 'description': 'Create issue #19 (live forecast orchestrator)'}
